The Budapest Stock Exchange (BSE) was re-opened in 1990 with headquarters in Budapest, Hungary.
The derivatives market of the BSE in futures and options contracts has been available to investors since 1995.
Effective 1 July 2002, the Budapest Stock Exchange Company Ltd. was set up (and from April 2006, as a Private Limited Company) and  the BSE Council and BSE Secretariat were replaced by a Board of Directors and an Executive Board.
